.SH "CAVEATS"
.PP
If a command
is executed, and then a command with the same name is
installed in a directory in the search path before the directory where the
original command was found, the shell will continue to
\fIexec\^\fP the original command\&.
Use the
\fB-t\fP option of the
\fBalias\^\fP command to correct this situation\&.
.PP
Some very old shell scripts contain a
\fB^\fP as a synonym for the pipe character
\fB\(or\fP\&.
.PP
Using the
\fBhist\^\fP built-in command within a compound command will cause the whole
command to disappear from the history file\&.
.PP
The built-in command \fB\!\&.\fP \fIfile\^\fP
reads the whole file before any commands are executed\&.
Therefore,
\fBalias\fP and
\fBunalias\fP commands in the file
will not apply to any commands defined in the file\&.
.PP
Traps are not processed while a job is waiting for a foreground process\&.
Thus, a trap on
\fBCHLD\fP won\&'t be executed until the foreground job terminates\&.
